This directory contains Ibis, a programming environment for wide-area
distributed computing in standard Java.

Ibis is free software.  See the file Copyright for copying permission.

The file INSTALL contains installation information, including prequisite
software.

The programmer's manual in this directory (progman.ps or progman.pdf)
contains a detailed description of the Ibis Application Programmer's
interface (API), illustrated with example code fragments.

The apps directory contains a large collection of example programs.
Unfortunately, in the current release there is no overview of the
examples.

The file BUGS contains information for filing bug reports.

The home page of Ibis is at: <http://www.cs.vu.nl/ibis/>.
